##HONG KONG ANTI-EPIDEMIC RECORD: One Public Rental Housing Two residents confirmed, unsealed exhaust suspected spread

I-CAIJING

Preliminary investigation revealed that the second confirmed case lived in a room with a drainage pipe connected to the exhaust pipe, the exhaust pipe is not sealed

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Although Hong Kong has not yet closed the community, a variety of crowded places are not closed for business. But when people are out and about, they are already very aware of the longer distances between them.

By Jiao Jian, special correspondent, Caijing

Editor | Susie

At 3:37 a.m. on February 11, the Centre for Health Protection of the Health Department of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region Government of China (hereinafter referred to as the CHP) announced that in order to intercept the potential risk of further spread of the novel coronavirus, the centre is actively following up on the confirmed cases of COVID-19 infection at Hong Mei House.

Completed in 1986 as public housing, Hong Mei House is located in Cheung Hong Estate, Tsing Yi district, Hong Kong. On February 10, a 62 year old woman living in the building was confirmed as the 42nd case of COVID-19 in Hong Kong; on January 30, the 12th case of COVID-19 in Hong Kong was also living in the building.

The two confirmed cases live on different floors. The female patient's room is located on the lower floor. The rooms are A1307 and A307, which are units 07 in the same building (unit) . Preliminary investigation showed that the second confirmed case lived in a room with a drainage pipe connected to the exhaust pipe, and the exhaust pipe was not sealed.

February 11 at about 0:45, a number of people involved in the preliminary investigation held a news conference to disclose the situation. Xie Zhanhuan, deputy director of the Environment Bureau of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region government of China, said that the u-shaped water traps in the two patients'units were found to be without problems. (the u-shaped water traps were designed to connect with kitchen basins or lavatory basins, so as not to dry up the air-isolating positions by using the handdishes.). Further investigation will include whether the two cases are related to building design and maintenance. Engineers will check whether the exhaust pipes of the same unit in the whole building are all sealed.

Professor Yuen Kwok-yung, chair professor of the Department of Microbiology, the University of Hong Kong, who participated in the preliminary survey, pointed out that the same number of units in the building share a dung channel, and the Dung Channel exhaust pipe is connected to the interior. The exhaust pipe in the female patient's room is not completely sealed, and the vent air can enter the room when the vent is opened, not excluding the possibility of the virus entering from there.

"The route of transmission of [ the novel coronavirus ] is not entirely clear... could it be airborne under special circumstances? " Yuen Kwok-yung said the possibilities include droplets, contact or airborne transmission. But he also stressed: Kang Meilou temporarily does not seem to be the SARS period in 2003 Amoy Big Garden e block (through the u-shaped water trap to spread the virus to many people sick) copy.

In March 2003,329 people in Block E of Amoy Gardens in Hong Kong were infected and 42 died, according to a report in Caijing. A subsequent investigation report released by the Hong Kong SAR Government of China showed that Amoy had spread on a large scale. It is believed that virus-carrying faeces entered the sewers and the unit u-shaped water collector dried up and could not be isolated from the air, the virus then travels with the airflow through the pipe, successfully passing through the airflow into the house and causing a massive outbreak. The World Health Organization report said the unusual outbreak in block e of Amoy Gardens may have been related to the design of the bathroom ventilation fan, which could have carried droplets from the bathroom to the patio or pumped into the bathroom from a cracked sewage drain, that infected a house a few floors apart.

Having learnt from the experience of Amoy Gardens, the guidelines on household cleaning and disinfection in the Hong Kong SAR of China have stressed the importance of proper maintenance of drainage pipes and regular filling of about half a litre of fresh water into every drainage outlet (U-TYPE grout) . In addition, when going to the toilet, you should cover the toilet plate before flushing the water to avoid spreading germs. However, the recommendations of the relevant sectors on the inclusion of separate dung channels and wastewater channels, separate high-and low-rise Drainage Channels in the buildings ordinance have not yet been fully implemented.

In recent cases of COVID-19 infection in Inner Mongolia, there have been "no travel, no contact history, living in confirmed cases of infection upstairs" example. According to Xinhua News, February 3, the Ordos City city of Dalat Banner Epidemic Prevention and Control Command conducted a briefing, said: by the DALAD Banner Department of Disease Control and Prevention on the flag of the fourth confirmed case of the Bai so-and-so tissue epidemiological investigation found that, it is the first confirmed case of the banner song a upstairs residents, Song a door and window often open, the door often have garbage heaps. During a white so-and-so many times up and down the stairs after a song. Wang and song a family has contact history, and Bai and his wife Zhang have a long history of close contact. According to the situation analysis, it can not be ruled out that song is the source of the COVID-19 pneumonia of the couple, Wang, according to a report from the DALAD Banner Epidemic Prevention and Control Command.

At present, "Kang Meilou" the chain of infection is not final. After the relevant news was announced, quite a number of Hong Kong people have expressed their concern, "I used to think that you could just watch out for the water in all the air ducts in your home, but now it turns out there are a lot of other things that you might need to watch out for, and you just can't watch out for them. "

Recently, some members of Hong Kong's building surveying industry warned that hot water should not be poured into drains at present. This is usually done to prevent mosquito breeding, but because the current period of transmission of the virus, if there is a virus in the canal, hot water may produce fog, but the virus into the indoor volatilization.

Since the early morning of February 11, more than 30 families and about 100 residents of Unit 07 on the first to 35th floors of the Kangmei building have been evacuated. They are taking a number of tour buses to their designated locations, the four quarantine centres (Lady maclehose Holiday Village, Lei Yue Mun Park Holiday Village, Pak Tam Chung Holiday camp and the newly opened Tsui Nga Shan House in the Jao Tsung-i Academy) have been opened in Hong Kong. Residents of other buildings in the residential area told CAIJING: Since around 7 a.m. , a large number of relevant personnel wearing protective clothing arrived at Kangmei building to carry out disinfection work, police vehicles and riot police officers also cordoned off the outside of the building.

In response to the continued spread of the COVID-19, the water supplies department of the Hong Kong SAR government of China has recently increased the chlorine content in drinking water from 1 mg / L to about 1.2 mg / l, to enhance the protection of fresh water in the transport and storage process to maintain cleanliness and hygiene.

The secretary of the Food and Health Bureau of the government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region of China, Chen Zhaoshi, also appealed to members of the public to maintain appropriate social distance recently, and strongly advised operators of crowded places such as cinemas, Karaoke establishments, clubs and tutorial centres to suspend business, says the next two weeks will be key to fighting the disease. She pointed out that the 18 districts in Hong Kong would not be closed and people staying at home was already a closed measure to reduce transmission.

As of 12:00 noon on February 11th, the number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in Hong Kong had risen to 42, with one patient dead. Of the more than 1,100 people under mandatory quarantine, nine were in breach of quarantine orders, and two were out of contact.
